11 period shall cause the forfeiture of all retirement benefits
12 received during the period; and
13 2. Unless otherwise provided in this section, earnings from
14 employment undertaken pursuant to this section may not exceed one-
15 half (1/2) of the member's final average salary used in computing
16 retirement benefits, or the earnings limitation for employees
17 allowed by the Social Security Administration, whichever is less.
18 For retired members under the age of sixty-two (62) years, the limit
19 on allowed earnings from a district attorney's office for employment
